31/05/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The heads of the intelligences services of the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia - met on Saturday (29 May) to discuss co-operation. They exchanged views on ways to implement army reforms and achieve NATO standards. They also discussed establishment of a sub-regional security system to strengthen the Alliance's southern flank.
Also Saturday, the government announced that Prime Minister Fatos Nano has invited the leaders of Macedonia, Serbia-Montenegro and Bosnia and Herzegovina to an informal meeting in June. Albania has stressed that one of its diplomatic priorities is to maintain good relations with its neighbours. (MIA - 30/05/04; Gazeta Shqiptare - 28/05/04)
